Name: Spread Eagle (band)
rawData:
Spread Eagle  is an American hard rock band from New York City, New York, United States. After only a few months of formation they were signed by MCA/Universal Records. They've released three albums: Spread Eagle (1990),  Open To The Public (1993) and Subway To The Stars (2019).
Spread Eagle's bassist Rob De Luca is also a member of British rock band UFO.
In the late 1980s, founding members Paul DiBartolo, Rob De Luca and Tommi Gallo were playing in the Boston-based hard rock band Bang. In September 1986, Bang won the MTV Basement Tapes competition with the video for their song "Summertime".

Origin: New York City, New York, United States
Labels: Frontiers Records, MCA/Universal Records, Lovember Records
